Several of my drafts had no test log but I kept getting questions like  I wrote the test log trying to show the Foundation figuring out the function in as few steps as possible.

I did try to keep it interesting with the incident involving Researcher Helm and the last test, and I'll look at changing up the last test, but I honestly don't know how else to show the process and make it interesting without bloating the test log further than it already is.

As far as the  list for it's anomalous effect, it was under the Testing  tab, but Baronjoe pointed out that knowing who the gun will target would be important information and should be presented with the Containment Procedures .

Your thoughts?





